Reds players, staff and supporters are mourning the loss of one of the club's all-time greats Liverpool have announced the death of legendary forward Ian St John at the age of 82. The Reds posted a message confirming St John's passing via social media on Tuesday, which reads: "We are deeply saddened by the passing of a true Anfield legend, Ian St John. "The thoughts of everyone at Liverpool Football Club are with Ian's family and friends at this sad and difficult time. Rest in peace, Ian St John 1938-2021."